<m0>THE BRIDGES <ql>
OF MADISON<ql>
COUNTY<ql>
<m0>(star)(star)(star) 1/2 <m0>Robert James Waller's phenomenally bestselling (and critically reviled) melodrama about a farm wife's affair with a photographer in 1965 Iowa has been turned into a resonant, richly rewarding film. Clint Eastwood and Meryl Streep play the lovers, and both deliver haunting, Oscar-caliber performances that amplify the story's themes of impossible love, sacrifice and devotion. Eastwood, who also directed in typical languorous fashion, has turned Waller's purple prose into something much greater. (--) <m0>Rene Rodriguez<m0> (PG-13,<m0> <m0>vulgar language, brief nudity, sexual situations.) (1995, Warner, 135 minutes.)<ql>
