<m0>AN UNFORGETTABLE SUMMER<ql>
<m0>(star)(star) 1/2<m0> A gentle tragedy set in 1925 Romania about a married noblewoman for whom no good deed goes unpunished. She is gracefully played by Kristin Scott-Thomas, who chooses to see individuals as humans rather than as members of ethnic groups. The plot is gauze-thin; the heroine's character is solid. In French, Romanian and Bulgarian with English subtitles. <m0>(--) Knight-Ridder Newspapers <m0>(No MPAA rating; nudity, violence, sex.) (1994, New Yorker, $89.95, 82 minutes.)<ep>
