<m0>WAITING TO EXHALE<m2><ql>
<m0>(star)(star)<m0> Terry McMillan's bestselling novel about the friendship between four lovelorn African-American women has been turned into a glib, shallow male-bashing tract that is a better conversation starter than it is a piece of human drama. Angela Bassett shines as a woman unexpectedly hurled into a messy divorce, and Wesley Snipes does wonders in a cameo role as the man who helps her out of her emotional shell shock, but the rest of the cast (including Whitney Houston, in a stiff and cold performance) fares badly, and Forest Whitaker directs with all the finesse of a half-hour sitcom. <m0>(--) Rene Rodriguez <m0>(R; vulgar language, sexual situations.) (1995, Fox, $19.98, 124 minutes.)<ep>
