<m0>STEAL BIG, STEAL LITTLE<m2><ql>
<m0>(star) <m0>Andy Garcia does double duty in this failed fable as twin brothers, one good and one bad, doing battle over a fat inheritance, but even his considerable charm can't save this misguided dud. Director Andrew Davis (<m0>The Fugitive<m0>)<m0>  <m0>seems to have forgotten how to make a good movie: This comedy, reportedly a pet project of his, is wildly overlong, unfocused, and so scattershot it's hard to say what Davis' intent was. A massive misfire. <m0>(--) Rene Rodriguez <m0>(PG-13;<m0> <m0>vulgar language, brief violence.) (1995, Savoy/HBO, 135 minutes; available on video disc.)<ql>
